<title>PHILIPPINES: Manila bourse urges firms to widen ownership base.</title>
<headline>Manila bourse urges firms to widen ownership base.</headline>
<dateline>MANILA 1997-07-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Philippine Stock Exchange (PSE) will ask 23 listed firms to expand their stockholders' base to more than 500.</p>
<p>Documents from the exchange obtained on Wednesday showed that trading of the companies may be suspended if they do not comply with the minimum shareholders requirement.</p>
<p>The minimum shareholders rule ensures that the companies remain public.</p>
<p>As of end-June, there were 23 firms with less than 500 shareholders, the exchange said.</p>
